    "summary": "I was born in 1953 in Corpus Christi, Texas USA. I grew up in Texas, went to college in Colorado, spent two years in Berlin and then moved to the Netherlands. I went into ministry, serving a congregation and then for a longer period working as a chaplain in psychiatric care and as an ethical consultant in care for those with a mental handicap. In 2008 I moved into a teaching and research position, first as a lecturer in health care ethics, and then in spiritual care and chaplaincy. With Sjaak K\u00f6rver of Tilburg School of Theology I now lead the Dutch Case Studies Project in Chaplaincy Studies. See below.",
