                    "company": "Protestant Theological University",
                    "description": "In 2014 I received an appointment as Professor in Spiritual Care & Chaplaincy Studies ('Bijzonder hoogleraar geestelijke verzorging') on behalf of the foundation 'Deo Volente', an organization in The Hague that financially supports research and educational initiatives in the fields of spiritual care and chaplaincy in health care. The position was at the Protestant Theological University in Groningen where I worked as a lecturer from 2008 on. In 2019 I retired.\nI am still coordinating the Dutch Case Studies Project in Chaplaincy Studies in which more than sixty chaplains and 10 academic researchers are participating. The project is part of the University Center for Chaplaincy Studies (ucgv.nl), a joint effort of the Protestant Theological University and Tiblurg School of Catholic Theology.\nUntil my retirement in 2019 I chaired the Academic Advisory Board of the Dutch Association of Spiritual Caregivers.\nYou can have a look at my academic webpages https://www.pthu.nl/Over_PThU/Organisatie/Medewerkers/m.walton/",
